Time Travel Using Lubridate

Can Taylor Swift make it to the Super Bowl?

We can use lubridate to see if Taylor Swift can make to her concert in Las Vegas after performing in Tokyo a day earlier. As you read the steps to the right within the R chunk, you see that Taylor indeed makes the Superbowl (which actually did happen in real life). This code assumes she rests on her flight from Las Vegas to Tokyo (does not take a break) and also immediately gets to the Allegiant Stadium once she reaches Las Vegas. We also have a timetospare variable that says how many hours she actually has to spare until the game starts.

suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(lubridate))

# Taylor's concert start time
StartofConcert <- ymd_hms("2024-02-10 18:00:00", tz = "Asia/Tokyo")

# Add 5 hours to get the concert end time
EndOfConcert <- StartofConcert + hours(5)

# Approximate duration from Tokyo to Las Vegas
DurationofFlight <- hours(12) + minutes(45)

# Get the arrival time to Las Vegas
ArrivalInVegas <- EndOfConcert + DurationofFlight

# Super Bowl start time in Las Vegas
StartofSB <- ymd_hms("2024-02-11 15:30:00", tz = "America/Los_Angeles")

# Check if Taylor can make it to the Super Bowl
SheCanMakeIt <- ArrivalInVegas < StartofSB

#Print if she makes it or not
if (SheCanMakeIt) {
  print("Taylor can make it to the Super Bowl!")
} else {
  print("Taylor can't make it to the Super Bowl.")
}
[1] "Taylor can make it to the Super Bowl!"
# "Taylor can make it to the Super Bowl!"
hours_and_minutes <- as.numeric(ArrivalInVegas) / 3600
hours_and_minutes <- as.numeric(StartofSB) / 3600

#Time to spare until Superbowl once she lands in Vegas
 timetospare <- StartofSB - ArrivalInVegas
timetospare

We can use lubridate to see if Taylor Swift can make to her concert in Las Vegas after performing in Tokyo a day earlier. As you read the steps to the right within the R chunk, you see that Taylor indeed makes the Superbowl (which actually did happen in real life). This code assumes she rests on her flight from Las Vegas to Tokyo (does not take a break) and also immediately gets to the Allegiant Stadium once she reaches Las Vegas. We also have a timetospare variable that says how many hours she actually has to spare until the game starts.

```{r}
suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(lubridate))

# Taylor's concert start time
StartofConcert <- ymd_hms("2024-02-10 18:00:00", tz = "Asia/Tokyo")

# Add 5 hours to get the concert end time
EndOfConcert <- StartofConcert + hours(5)

# Approximate duration from Tokyo to Las Vegas
DurationofFlight <- hours(12) + minutes(45)

# Get the arrival time to Las Vegas
ArrivalInVegas <- EndOfConcert + DurationofFlight

# Super Bowl start time in Las Vegas
StartofSB <- ymd_hms("2024-02-11 15:30:00", tz = "America/Los_Angeles")

# Check if Taylor can make it to the Super Bowl
SheCanMakeIt <- ArrivalInVegas < StartofSB

#Print if she makes it or not
if (SheCanMakeIt) {
  print("Taylor can make it to the Super Bowl!")
} else {
  print("Taylor can't make it to the Super Bowl.")
}
# "Taylor can make it to the Super Bowl!"
hours_and_minutes <- as.numeric(ArrivalInVegas) / 3600
hours_and_minutes <- as.numeric(StartofSB) / 3600

#Time to spare until Superbowl once she lands in Vegas
 timetospare <- StartofSB - ArrivalInVegas
timetospare 
```
